          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>10 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: Marcel 68; Qurʾānic Text: Q 48:20-49:1; 5 lines per page; Dimensions:  328 x 228mm; Script style: kūfi D.III.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The fragments <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/626/page/1r">Arabe 351</ref> (BNF) and maybe <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2280/page/1r">Marcel 64</ref>, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2288/page/1r">Marcel 69</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2289/page/1r">Marcel 71</ref> (NLR) belong to the same manuscript.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The catalogue entry by Valery V. Polosin (1939-2014) contains the following information:</p>
              <p>"<hi rend="bold">Marcel 68</hi></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Fragment</hi>: <hi rend="bold">48</hi>:20(20)–29(29)*, title of surah <hi rend="bold">49</hi>.</p>
              <p>10 fol. 228×328 мм (1.44). <hi rend="bold">Support</hi>: thin transparent parchment of yellowish color. <hi rend="bold">Writing material</hi>: dark brown, almost black ink.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Collation</hi>: one quire, fol. 3 and 8 are singletons with stubs, the rest are bifolia.</p>
              <p>I: H1F H2F H3F<hi rend="italic">S</hi> H4F H5F / F6H F7H F8H<hi rend="italic">S</hi> F9H F10H.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Text layout</hi>: 100×200 mm (2.0), 5 lines.<hi rend="bold"> Ruling</hi>: absent.<hi rend="bold"> Script</hi>: bold D III.<hi rend="bold"> Diacritics</hi>: absent. <hi rend="bold">Vocalization</hi>: large round dots of red, blue and green color.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Verse markers</hi>: for individual verses – teardrop-shaped medallions in the text line (type 4.1.1) in gold and colors, with the inscribed word اية; for groups of five verses – medallions in the text line (type 3.B.II) drawn in gold and colors with the inscribed word خمس (л. 5r, 10v); for groups of 10 verses – medallions in the text line (type 2.А.II), in gold and colors, with the inscribed word عشر (fol. 1r).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Title of surah 49</hi> (سورة الحجرات ثمان عشرة) is written in gold and inscribed in a rectangular panel with geometric patterns, the inner space of which is filled with floral patterns dran in pale red ink; with adjacent large palmetto drawn in gold on the margin (fol. 10v).<hi rend="underline"> </hi></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Stitching</hi>: thread has preserved in the punctures of the fold. </p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Inscriptions</hi>: number of the surahs in Roman numerals and the verse number in Arabic numerals are inscribed on the upper margin of the first page; on all other sheets similar numbers are written by pencil on the upper margins; pagination in pencil on the upper margin.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Defects</hi>: traces of moisture on fol. 1–5, the text partly blurred; the outer bifolium damaged along the fold. </p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Attached materials</hi>: old wrapping (fol. I) consisting of a narrow strip of paper inscribed with the letters “<hi rend="italic">S</hi>”, brief description of the manuscript in French in brown ink and old accession number in red pencil “<hi rend="italic">B. 45”; on the verso side inscription in French “Monsieur Merlin</hi>”. Small sheet of paper (fol. II) with annotation in Arabic, in <hi rend="italic">naskhi</hi> script and brown ink: “الابتداء وجه / ٤٦٦ /سورو الفتح / اية  /٢٠ /و الاخر الى وجه /٤٢٨ /ابتد سورة الحجرات”.<hi rend="underline"/></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Old accession numbers</hi>: S. (on the wrapping), B. 45 (on the wrapping and according to Langlois’ inventory).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Contents</hi>:</p>
              <p>Fol. 1r–10v. Surah 48, verses 20(20)-29(29)*. Incipit: [لكم هذه وكف أيد]ي الناس عنكم . Explicit: أجرا عظيما [بسم الله الرحمن] .</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Other fragments of the same manuscript</hi>: Marcel 64(?), Marcel 69(?),Marcel 71(?) (NLR); Arabe 351 (BNF)".</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Olga Yastrebova has translated and sometimes corrected the notes of V. Polosin. Corrected passages are marked with ОЯ (O.Ya).</p>
            </summary>
